        "subject": "LU-1199 rpm: modules always use the .ko extension",
        "message": "LU-1199 rpm: modules always use the .ko extension\n\nThere's an if/elif stanza to check whether a module is present with a\n.ko or .o extension. Since the beginning of 2.6.x kernel series,\nmodules have had a .ko extension.\n\nThere's no need to check for the .o extension.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jeff Mahoney <jeffm@suse.com>\nChange-Id: I54c30c133aba213a8d67d743f8a86798aad8f208\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
